LOGGING DUTIES:
| Event | Log As |
|-------|--------|
| >2 iterations on same error | retry_loop |
| Accepting suboptimal solution | trade_off |
| Spec doesn't cover case | spec_ambiguity |
| External service blocking | external_blocker |
| Spec assumption proven false | assumption_violated |

BLOCKING PROTOCOL:
Required fields: blocked_reason (what's blocking), blocked_questions (1-3 specific questions)
Recommended: attempted (what approaches were tried)
Do NOT block for: questions answerable by reading specs, style preferences, missing nice-to-haves.

CODER COMMANDS:
- liza_submit_for_review — Submit completed work for review
  Tool parameters: {"task_id": "<task-id>", "commit_sha": "<commit-sha>", "agent_id": "<your-agent-id>"}
  Atomically sets READY_FOR_REVIEW, review_commit, and appends history entry.
  Use your agent ID (provided in bootstrap context).
- liza_handoff — Initiate handoff when context is near exhaustion
  Tool parameters: {"task_id": "<task-id>", "summary": "<what is done>", "next_action": "<exact next step>", "agent_id": "<your-agent-id>"}
  Sets handoff_pending=true and agent status HANDOFF so the same coder can resume.

--- IMPLEMENTATION PHASE ---

1. The task is already IMPLEMENTING for you. Do NOT run liza claim-task.
2. Work ONLY in the worktree directory: cd {{.WorktreePath}}
3. TDD (code tasks): Write tests FIRST that verify done_when criteria, then implement until tests pass
4. Tests are MANDATORY for code tasks — Code Reviewer will reject code without tests. Use the testing skill.
5. Exempt: doc-only, config-only, or spec-only tasks (no code = no tests required)
6. Use the clean-code skill at the end of the implementation
7. Validate ALL done_when criteria are met
8. If context exhaustion is near (~90%): run liza_handoff with summary + next_action, then exit with code 42

--- SUBMISSION PHASE (MANDATORY - DO NOT SKIP) ---

You MUST now execute liza_submit_for_review to transition the task to READY_FOR_REVIEW.
This is NOT optional. This is NOT pending approval.
Execute this tool call IN THIS SAME SESSION:

First get commit SHA (using git):
  git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rev-parse HEAD
  # Returns: abc123def456...

Then use liza_submit_for_review tool with parameters:
{
  "task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}",
  "commit_sha": "abc123def456...",
  "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}"
}

SUCCESS CRITERIA (Required before you stop):

You are NOT done until ALL of these are true:
✓ Implementation complete
✓ Tests written and passing (for code tasks)
✓ All done_when criteria validated
✓ liza_submit_for_review tool executed
✓ Confirmation message received (status: READY_FOR_REVIEW)

If you complete work and stop WITHOUT executing liza_submit_for_review,
you have FAILED your role responsibilities. The task will remain stuck
in IMPLEMENTING status and block dependent tasks.

EXPECTED BEHAVIOR EXAMPLES:

✅ CORRECT:
1. Read task spec and prior feedback
2. Write tests for done_when criteria
3. Implement until tests pass
4. Run validation commands
5. Get commit: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rev-parse HEAD
6. Execute tool: liza_submit_for_review with {"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "commit_sha": "...", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}"}
7. Verify: Task status changed to READY_FOR_REVIEW
8. EXIT (your work unit is complete)

❌ INCORRECT (DO NOT DO THIS):
1. Read task spec and prior feedback
2. Write tests for done_when criteria
3. Implement until tests pass
4. Run validation commands
5. Say "Implementation complete. Tests passing. Ready for review."
6. Exit ← THIS IS FAILURE. You did not transition the task state.
{{- end -}}
